        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 12:58AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1257 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
south of Chouteau, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Salina...                         Chouteau...
Peggs...                          Sportsmen Acres Community...
Mazie...                          Murphy...
Snowdale State Park...            Locust Grove...
Pryor Creek...                    Wagoner...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
